    <interface name="InfoProvider"
               c:symbol-prefix="info_provider"
               c:type="NautilusInfoProvider"
               glib:type-name="NautilusInfoProvider"
               glib:get-type="nautilus_info_provider_get_type"
               glib:type-struct="InfoProviderInterface">
      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
           line="28">Interface to provide additional information about files

`NautilusInfoProvider` allows extension to provide additional information about
files. When [method@InfoProvider.update_file_info] is called by the application,
extensions will know that it's time to add extra information to the provided
[iface@FileInfo].</doc>
      <source-position filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.h"
                       line="84"/>
      <function name="update_complete_invoke"
                c:identifier="nautilus_info_provider_update_complete_invoke">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
             line="107">Complete an async file info update.</doc>
        <source-position filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.h"
                         line="94"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <type name="none" c:type="void"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <parameter name="update_complete" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
                 line="109">the closure to call</doc>
            <type name="GObject.Closure" c:type="GClosure*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="provider" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
                 line="110">an info provider</doc>
            <type name="InfoProvider" c:type="NautilusInfoProvider*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="handle" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
                 line="111">the handle for the given closure</doc>
            <type name="OperationHandle" c:type="NautilusOperationHandle*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="result" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
                 line="112">either `NAUTILUS_OPERATION_COMPLETE` or `NAUTILUS_OPERATION_FAILED`</doc>
            <type name="OperationResult" c:type="NautilusOperationResult"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </function>
      <virtual-method name="cancel_update" invoker="cancel_update">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libnautilus-extension/nautilus-info-provider.c"
             line="80">Called when the Nautilus application has canceled an update.

This method is only relevant if [method@InfoProvider.update_file_info] was returned with
`NAUTILUS_OPERATION_IN_PROGRESS`.</doc>
